SUMMARY:Digital Open-Source Investigations: Geolocation Webinar
DESCRIPTION:An NAHJ webinar training series for 2026: Digital Open-Source Investigations and OSINT for Journalism\n\nGeolocation \nParticipants will learn how to verify images and videos by finding exactly where they were recorded using satellite and street-view imagery from platforms like Google Earth and Maps. \nWhen: Thursday\, March 19\, 2026\nTime: 6:00 PM – 7:15 PM EST\nRegister: https://nahj.memberclicks.net/OSINTgeo \nPresented by: OSINT Reporting Lab at USC Annenberg School for Communication and Journalism  \n  \n 
URL:https://nahj.org/event/digital-open-source-investigations-geolocation-webinar/
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://nahj.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/NAHJ_OpenSource-7.png
END:VEVENT
