SUMMARY:Digital Open-Source Investigations: Open Search Webinar
DESCRIPTION:An NAHJ webinar training series for 2026: Digital Open-Source Investigations and OSINT for Journalism\n\nOpen Search \nParticipants will learn how search engines work\, the varieties of search engines\, and how to craft advanced search queries to find exactly what they are looking for on the internet\, discover new sources of information\, and uncover information hiding in plain sight. \nWhen: Wednesday\, April 8\, 2026\nTime: 6:00 PM – 7:15 PM EST\nRegister: https://nahj.memberclicks.net/OSINTopensearch \nPresented by: OSINT Reporting Lab at USC Annenberg School for Communication and Journalism  \n 
URL:https://nahj.org/event/digital-open-source-investigations-open-search-webinar/
CATEGORIES:Webinar
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://nahj.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/NAHJ_OpenSource-8.png
